                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15106646" author="dancollins" created="Tue, 19 Jan 2016 12:14:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a dump of a git patch, but should be good enough to let you apply it to trunk and 5.5.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15106704" author="cpoerschke" created="Tue, 19 Jan 2016 13:32:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting this and providing a patch. I am not (yet) locally set up for and familiar with Maven builds, so it may take me a little while to take care of this as a follow-on to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-839&quot; title=&quot;XML Query Parser support (deftype=xmlparser)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-839&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-839&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. (If in the meantime anyone else is already set up and more familiar, feel free to grab this ticket from me.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15107078" author="erickerickson" created="Tue, 19 Jan 2016 17:56:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Last I knew, the Maven version is not &quot;officially&quot; supported, it&apos;s there as a convenience so I don&apos;t think backporting to 5.4 is strictly necessary.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s backport it anyway to 5.4 so it would be included in any re-spin, but in and of itself it&apos;s not going to justify a respin of 5.4, especially with the Git stuff happening (tentatively) this weekend IMO.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15107099" author="dancollins" created="Tue, 19 Jan 2016 18:06:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=erickerickson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;erickerickson&quot;&gt;erickerickson&lt;/a&gt; The references to 5.4 were my bad, I&apos;m back-porting to our internal 5.4.x branch which was what confused me, so apologies for that.  I&apos;ve updated my comment now to correct that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The only versions that are broken are 5.5 and trunk, so only &quot;unreleased&quot; branches.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wonder if anyone (else) used the Maven build process, wasn&apos;t sure of its status, but I figured it wasn&apos;t really used much.  For any projects which are dependent on Lucene (e.g. Luwak), maven seems to be a more convenient build mechanism, so we do make use of it, but I don&apos;t know who else does!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15107124" author="erickerickson" created="Tue, 19 Jan 2016 18:19:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;NP. And yes, others do use the Maven build process but AFAIK, it&apos;s not exercised nearly as much as the ant version, so it lags at times.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15109324" author="steve_rowe" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 20:20:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I looked at the patch on this issue, and I don&apos;t think adding the queryparser module&apos;s test .class files to the test phase classpath via a testResource is the way to go.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maven has a standard mechanism for this, which is used elsewhere in the build (e.g. the dih-extras module has a test dependency on the dih module&apos;s tests): maven-jar-plugin:test-jar will generate a jar of test classes on the producer module side, and then the consumer module depends on this jar via a test-scope dependency of type &lt;tt&gt;test-jar&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll work up a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15109340" author="steve_rowe" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 20:31:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that fixes solr-core test compilation for me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running all tests now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15110084" author="steve_rowe" created="Thu, 21 Jan 2016 05:32:07 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Patch that fixes solr-core test compilation for me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running all tests now.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All tests pass with the exception of a couple that are not related.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committing shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
